		<body>

			<h1> Team Questions. 1) h1 formating for p answers. 2) Store Associated Arrays? </h1>
			<h1> *Local Storage </h1>
				
				<p> Stores data in the browser with no expiration date. </p>
				<p> Information will not be lost when the tab is closed. </p>
				<p> Local Storage is an object, which mean info must be stored in name-value pairs. </p>
			<hr>	
				<h2> Save and Load an Object to Local Storage </p>
					
					<p> Who is the creepiest hero ever? </p>
					<button onclick="saveObject()"> Save and Load the Object </button>
					<p id="demo_1"> </p>
					
					<script>
					
					function saveObject() {
						if (typeof(Storage) !== "undefined") {

						//Saving Object:
						myHero = { codeName: "Batman", age: 27, city: "Gotham" };
						JSONHero = JSON.stringify(myHero);
						localStorage.setItem("HeroJSON", JSONHero);
						
						//Loading Object:
						text = localStorage.getItem("HeroJSON");
						myHero = JSON.parse(text);
						document.getElementById("demo_1").innerHTML = myHero.codeName;
						} else {
								alert("Sorry, there's no web storage support on this browser!");
							}
					}
					
					</script>
		
			<hr>
				<h2> Save an Array to Local Storage </p>
					
					<p> How many baddies has Bond taken out? </p>
					<button onclick="saveArray()"> Save and Load the Array </button>
					<p id="demo_2" style="font-size:12px"> </p>

					<script>
				
					function saveArray() {
						if (typeof(Storage) !== "undefined") {
						
						//Saving Object:
						mySpy = { codeName: "007", age: 24, city: "London", killRoster: [ "Gold Finger", "Specter", "Dr. No" ] };
						JSONSpy = JSON.stringify(mySpy);
						localStorage.setItem("spyJSON", JSONSpy);
						
						//Loading Object:
						text = localStorage.getItem("spyJSON");
						mySpy = JSON.parse(text);
						document.getElementById("demo_2").innerHTML = mySpy.killRoster[0] + ", " 
						+ mySpy.killRoster[1] + ", " + mySpy.killRoster[2];
						} else {
							alert("Sorry, there's no web storage support on this browser!");
						}
					}
					</script>
		
		<hr>
				<h2> Save and Load a String </p>
					
					<p> How awesome is Bond? </p>
					<button onclick="saveBondString()"> Save and Load the String </button>
					<p id="demo_4"> </p>

					<script>
				
					function saveBondString() {
						if (typeof(Storage) !== "undefined") {
					//Saving Object:
					bondMotto = "Very awesome.";
					mottoJSON = JSON.stringify(bondMotto);
					localStorage.setItem("bondAnswer", mottoJSON);
					
					//Loading Object:
					text = localStorage.getItem("bondAnswer");
					riddleAnswer = JSON.parse(text);
					document.getElementById("demo_4").innerHTML = riddleAnswer;
					
					}else {
							alert("Sorry, there's no web storage support on this browser!");
						}
					}
					</script>
		<hr>
				<h2> Delete a Local Storage Object </p>
				
					<p> Who is the most powerful DC Superhero? </p>
					<button onclick="saveSuperman()"> Save and Load the Original Information </button>
					<p id="demo_5"> </p>
					
					<script>
					
					function saveSuperman() {
						if (typeof(Storage) !== "undefined") {

						//Saving Object:
						fileSuperman = { codeName: "Superman", age: 32, city: "Metropolis" };
						JSONSuperman = JSON.stringify(fileSuperman);
						localStorage.setItem("HeroJSON", JSONSuperman);
						
						//Loading Object:
						text = localStorage.getItem("HeroJSON");
						Superman = JSON.parse(text);
						document.getElementById("demo_5").innerHTML = Superman.codeName;
						} else {
								alert("Sorry, there's no web storage support on this browser!");
							}
					}
					
					</script>
					
					<button onclick="DeleteSuperman()"> Attempt to load the object after deletion </button>
					<p id="demo_6"> </p>
					
					<script>
					
					function DeleteSuperman() {
						if (typeof(Storage) !== "undefined") {

						//Saving Object:
						//fileSuperman = { codeName: "Superman", age: 32, city: "Metropolis" };
						//JSONSuperman = JSON.stringify(fileSuperman);
						//localStorage.setItem("HeroJSON", JSONSuperman);
						
						// Delete Entire "Superman" Property.
						// localStorage.clear('fileSuperman');
						
						// Delete a single name-value pair from the "Superman" Object.
							localStorage.removeItem("HeroJSON");
						
						//Loading Object:
							if (typeof(Storage) !== "undefined") {
								document.getElementById("demo_6").innerHTML = "Uh oh, there's nothing here.";
							} else {
							text = localStorage.getItem("HeroJSON");
							Superman = JSON.parse(text);
							document.getElementById("demo_6").innerHTML = Superman.codeName;
									}
							} else {
								alert("Sorry, there's no web storage support on this browser!");
									}
					}
					
					</script>
					
			
		<hr>	
			<h1> *Session Storage </h1>
				
				<p> Temporarily stores data. </p>
				<p> Information will be deleted when the tab is closed. </p>
				
				<p id="demo_7"></p>

				<script>
				function clickCounter() {
					if(typeof(Storage) !== "undefined") {
						if (sessionStorage.clickcount) {
							sessionStorage.clickcount = Number(sessionStorage.clickcount)+1;
						} else {
							sessionStorage.clickcount = 1;
							//document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = "I think Batman can take on " + sessionStorage.clickcount + " bad guy, in one session.";
						}
						document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = "I think Batman can take on " + sessionStorage.clickcount + " bad guys, in one session.";
					
					} else {
						document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = "Sorry, your browser does not support web storage...";
					}
				}
				</script>
				</script>

				<p><button onclick="clickCounter()" type="button">Click me!</button></p>
				<div id="result"></div>
				<p>How many bad guys do you think Batman can fight at once?</p>
				<p>If you close the browser tab to try again, you will notice that the counter has reset.</p>
		
		</body>	
	</html>
